~~~ ->pd ~~~

a simple python interface to pure data...

~~~ testing ~~~

run test.sh

~~~ hacking ~~~

open test.py... 

or try something like this on you python interpreter...

first... run pd...

   $ pd recebe.pd &

then... run python...

   $ python

so... line by line... with python on a window and recebe.pd on another...

   from topy import *
   p = Patch()
   osc = Object('osc~', '440', 100, 100)
   dac = Object('dac~', '', 100, 200)
   p.create(osc)
   p.create(dac)
   p.connect(osc, 0, dac, 0)
   p.connect(osc, 0, dac, 1)
   p.dsp(1)
   p.disconnect(osc, 0, dac, 0)
   p.delete(osc)
   p.dsp(0)

or something more exentric...

   from topy import *
   from random import randint
   p = Patch()
   dac = Object('dac~', '', 250, 250)
   p.create(dac)
   for i in range(0, 500):
       o = Object('osc~', str(i), randint(0, 500), randint(0, 500))
       p.create(o)
       p.connect(o, 0, dac, 0)
       p.connect(o, 0, dac, 1)

hope you enjoy...

